name: High School Musical: The Musical: The Series
original_name: High School Musical: The Musical: The Series
overview: A group of East High students countdown to the opening night of their school’s first-ever production of “High School Musical.” Showmances blossom; friendships are tested while new ones are made; rivalries flare and lives are changed forever as these young people discover the transformative power that only a high school drama club can provide.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In season two, the East High Wildcats, who are preparing to perform “Beauty and the Beast” as their spring musical, face off against rival school North High to win a prestigious and cutthroat student theater competition. Wigs are snatched, loyalties are tested, and ballads are belted!

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: After an epic summer at Camp Shallow Lake, the Wildcats return to East High where they prepare a stage production of "High School Musical 3: Senior Year." However, plans are disrupted when Principal Gutierrez announces that Disney has decided to make the long-awaited "High School Musical 4: The Reunion" movie on location at their beloved high school.

episodes.name: The Auditions
episodes.overview: Ricky decides to audition for East High's fall musical, "High School Musical," in an effort to rekindle his relationship with his ex-girlfriend Nini.

episodes.name: The Read-Through
episodes.overview: E.J. is jealous and reeling after losing the leading role of "Troy" to Ricky, and Miss Jenn tells the conflicted leading lady, Nini, to "trust the process."

episodes.name: The Wonderstudies
episodes.overview: After “losing” her phone and missing an important rehearsal, Nini suspects who is responsible for her bout with bad luck and surprisingly retaliates. EJ confronts Ricky about a heartfelt voicemail left for Nini. Meanwhile, Mr. Mazzara becomes suspicious of Miss Jenn's past.

episodes.name: Blocking
episodes.overview: After Nini discovers that E.J. isn’t who she thinks he is, Ashlyn gets caught in the middle. Gina and E.J. team up as “wonderstudies,” and Ricky gets an unexpected visitor at home.

episodes.name: Homecoming
episodes.overview: Miss Jenn organizes a girl’s night out with Kourtney and Nini to help Nini shake off the boy drama, while the rest of the theater kids attend the East High Homecoming dance, where Carlos learns to dance like everyone’s watching.

episodes.name: What Team?
episodes.overview: When Miss Jenn is placed on temporary leave and rehearsals are put on hold, the students rally together to defend their drama teacher.

episodes.name: Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: A rambunctious Thanksgiving "cast party" at Ashlyn's ends with surprising news for Gina, while Miss Jenn and Mr. Mazzara accidentally spend the holiday together at East High.

episodes.name: The Tech Rehearsal
episodes.overview: When the cast and crew unexpectedly need to find a new location to "tech" their production, Carlos secures a spooky theater downtown, forcing Miss Jenn to confront old demons.

episodes.name: Opening Night
episodes.overview: After months of rehearsals, the theater kids gear up for an unforgettable opening night. But when unexpected audience members show up to shake the cast to its core, will the show "go on" if the Wildcats aren't all in this together?

episodes.name: Act Two
episodes.overview: It's Act Two of opening night, and the stakes have never been higher. After last-minute cast changes in Act One — and so much left unsaid between Ricky and Nini — there's more drama offstage than on

episodes.name: New Year's Eve
episodes.overview: Flying high after the triumph of opening night, Ricky, Nini, Gina, and the Wildcats gather at Ashlyn's for a New Year's Eve party. Miss Jenn runs into the new North High rival theatre teacher—a.k.a her ex-boyfriend—and at the stroke of midnight, shocking revelations come to the surface.

episodes.name: Typecasting
episodes.overview: Kourtney, Carlos and Big Red decide to join their friends and audition for on stage roles in "Beauty and the Beast," while Nini experiences FOMO from afar. When new competition shows up to the tryout, Gina tries to shake off some old habits.

episodes.name: Valentine's Day
episodes.overview: Big Red and Ashlyn celebrate their first Valentine's Day together, amidst drama. Kourtney spars with a co-worker while Gina contends with being single. Meanwhile, Ricky and Nini's plans to surprise each other turn into a comedy of errors, leading to new revelations and a surprise song.

episodes.name: The Storm
episodes.overview: When a blizzard barrels down on Salt Lake City, the Wildcats are stranded at East High after hours, just as E.J. receives some bad news. As cabin fever sets in, Miss Jenn inspires Nini to make a bold choice about her future; Kourtney's coworker Howie makes a surprising move; and Gina and Carlos come to blows.

episodes.name: The Quinceañero
episodes.overview: Gina and Seb rally the group to throw Carlos the music and dance-filled Quinceañero he never had. Meanwhile, Ricky accidentally oversteps in more ways than one, and Miss Jenn gets a wild idea about how to get Nini back onstage at East High.

episodes.name: Yes, And...
episodes.overview: After rival school North High releases a viral video to undermine the Wildcats, Miss Jenn hosts a weekend improv intensive to build up her kids' confidence. Meanwhile, Nini works on a new song at Salt Lake Slices, where she finds inspiration in Kourtney's approach to life.

episodes.name: The Field Trip
episodes.overview: When the Wildcats suspect that North High has stolen a key costume piece, they infiltrate their rival school and end up in a competitive dance-off. Miss Jenn goes face to face and toe to toe with Zack Roy. And an emboldened Nini takes a big risk.

episodes.name: Most Likely To
episodes.overview: When the Wildcats are benched from rehearsal for a week, tensions rise to the surface during Career Day. Big Red questions if Ashlyn understands his dreams; Howie makes a surprising move with Kourtney; E.J. shocks his dad with a revelation; and Ricky and Nini visit an old haunt.

episodes.name: Spring Break
episodes.overview: When Gina finds herself stranded at the airport over Spring Break, a surprise run-in changes her mind about what she wants. Meanwhile, the separated Wildcats find a way to bond over song during their break, as Ricky finally sees his mom again after their opening night run-in at "High School Musical."

episodes.name: The Transformation
episodes.overview: After rehearsals fall flat, the cast breaks into separate sleepovers to brainstorm Broadway-worthy ideas to outdo North High. But as the countdown to opening night looms, secrets rise between Nini and Gina, Seb and Carlos suffer their first fight, and Ricky receives an unexpected FaceTime call.

episodes.name: Showtime
episodes.overview: It's opening night, and Nini hypes up her anxious castmates for their performance in front of the competition judge. But no East High opening night is complete without unexpected visitors, second chances, and big decisions about everyone's futures—together and apart.

episodes.name: Second Chances
episodes.overview: While the Wildcats head to Salt Lake Slices to digest the excitement of opening night - and a pizza or two - Miss Jenn continues to experience tunnel vision over the Menkie Awards. Mr. Mazzara shows his softer side; Ricky reevaluates a party crasher; Gina speaks her truth; and Nini makes a life-altering call.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: In season two, the East High Wildcats, who are preparing to perform “Beauty and the Beast” as their spring musical, face off against rival school North High to win a prestigious and cutthroat student theater competition. Wigs are snatched, loyalties are tested, and ballads are belted!

episodes.name: Happy Campers
episodes.overview: After a momentous year at East High, the Wildcats head to Camp Shallow Lake for two weeks of fun in the sun. With a high-stakes production of “Frozen” looming and new campers threatening to shake up the Wildcats’ dynamic, the campers are in for an unforgettable summer of highs, lows, and “Let It Go’s.”

episodes.name: Into the Unknown
episodes.overview: A reluctant E.J. takes the reins in a surprisingly new role on "Frozen". New campers bring vocal chops—and competition—to the auditions. In Los Angeles, Nini makes a potentially life-changing discovery of her own.

episodes.name: The Woman in the Woods
episodes.overview: After the cast list is revealed, the campers embark on Maddox's favourite camp tradition: Newbie Initiation Night. The centrepiece of the night is a spooky tale that sends Gina and Ricky on a quest into the unknown.

episodes.name: No Drama
episodes.overview: After a spooktacular night in the woods, the cast of "Frozen" have their first read-through. But the Wildcats are in disarray from Corbin Bleu's documentary crew and a camper's sudden disappearance.

episodes.name: The Real Campers of Shallow Lake
episodes.overview: After promising juicy drama for the "Frozen" documentary, E.J., Carlos and Val plan to turn rehearsals into "The Real Campers of Shallow Lake". But E.J. realizes he may have gone too far when the fake drama pushes some real buttons.

episodes.name: Color War
episodes.overview: After an explosive rehearsal, the Wildcats are divided into rivalries for an annual all-camp competition known as Color War.

episodes.name: Camp Prom
episodes.overview: A throwback '70s-themed prom unexpectedly inspires everyone to look to the future.

episodes.name: Let It Go
episodes.overview: Nerves run high on the opening night of "Frozen" as the documentary's release quickly approaches.

episodes.name: High School Musical 4
episodes.overview: Disney announces that "High School Musical 4: High School Reunion" will be shooting at East High.

episodes.name: HSM v. HSM
episodes.overview: The Wildcats contend with High School Musical 3 auditions AND High School Musical 4 rehearsal.

episodes.name: A Star is Reborn
episodes.overview: High School Musical 4 pulls focus from High School Musical 3 as one of the Wildcats has a star-is-born moment.

episodes.name: Trick or Treat
episodes.overview: At Gina's Halloween party, relationships are put to the test and secrets are revealed.

episodes.name: Admissions
episodes.overview: With Ricky and Kourtney off to college and the other Wildcats distracted, the musical is in peril.

episodes.name: Trust the Process
episodes.overview: The Wildcats revisit the past in order to secure the future of the theater program.

episodes.name: The Night of Nights
episodes.overview: Ricky, Gina, and the rest of the Wildcats must make big decisions on opening night of HSM 3.

episodes.name: Born to Be Brave
episodes.overview: Act Two of HSM 3 Opening Night is shaken up by surprise guests and looming decisions.

However, plans are disrupted when Principal Gutierrez announces that Disney has decided to make the long-awaited "High School Musical 4: The Reunion" movie on location at their beloved high school.
